    <p>Samsung's residential ice-maker reputation in LA is shaped by the 2017-2021 freeze-up service history: certain French-door models (RF23J, RF28HMED and family) developed ice-maker freeze-up and related cooling issues that resulted in multiple class-action settlements and service bulletins. Our approach on those serial ranges: we verify bulletin eligibility at diagnostic, apply any Samsung-authorized service-bulletin fixes (water-line heat-tape retrofit is the most common), and quote any out-of-warranty work at standard $89 diagnostic waived with repair. For current-generation Bespoke 4-door and Family Hub units, freeze-up patterns are different — Samsung's engineering changes on 2022+ units reduced the historical fault mode significantly.</p>
    <p>LA Samsung install base concentrates in mid-luxury remodels across Silver Lake + Studio City + Manhattan Beach + Pasadena + OC, with Bespoke 4-door showing up in design-forward kitchens where interchangeable panel color is a deliberate design choice. Our techs carry common Samsung modular ice-maker assemblies, water-inlet valves, and heat-tape kits on the truck. Samsung parts ship 1-3 day LA-local through authorized distribution.</p>
